# OTA Update System Guide

The Bear-Loader app supports Over-the-Air (OTA) updates for game variants and resources.

- [OTARepository.kt](mdc:app/src/main/java/com/bearmod/loader/data/repository/OTARepository.kt): Handles update checks, download logic, and update state.
- [OTAModels.kt](mdc:app/src/main/java/com/bearmod/loader/data/model/OTAModels.kt): Defines data models for OTA updates.
- UI for OTA is in [DownloadActivity.kt](mdc:app/src/main/java/com/bearmod/loader/ui/ota/DownloadActivity.kt), [UpdateAvailableActivity.kt](mdc:app/src/main/java/com/bearmod/loader/ui/ota/UpdateAvailableActivity.kt), and related fragments/adapters.

## OTA Flow
- The app checks for updates using OTARepository.
- Available updates are shown in the UI.
- Downloads and installations are managed by the repository and activities.

Refer to these files for implementing or modifying OTA update logic.

